<title><![CDATA[Yoghurt, Wheat and Chickpea Soup]]></title>
<description><![CDATA[Tangy, garlicky and fragrant, yoghurt soups are eaten across Eastern Europe, the Caucasus and into the Middle East. This soup is why nearly every village in Turkey and Armenia can boast at least one resident who at 100 years old can still dance a respectable tango. The combination of yoghurt, chickpeas and spelt or wheatberries is incredibly fortifying and nutritious.

Much as I hate the idea of using dried herbs, it really is essential to use dried mint in this recipe. To make your own, just lay a few handfuls of fresh mint leaves on a cloth on your radiator or on a sunny window ledge for a few hours, or place them in a low oven for 45 minutes.]]></description>
