<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[SautÃ© onion, mint, and salt for 4-5 minutes in oil and butter until the onion is soft]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add the chicken stock, spelt and chickpeas and bring the mixture to the boil.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[After 2-3 minutes, reduce the heat and simmmer 1 hr on low]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Stir in the chard, cook for a minute further, then switch off the heat.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[In a separate pot, combine the yoghurt, water, garlic, flour and egg and whisk together. Bring to boil over high heat and whisking constantly.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[As soon as it's boiled, stir it into the chicken stock mixture simmer 5 minutes, then remove and cool slightly. Season with salt and pepper.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Sizzle the mint in melted butter gently just until its colour and flavour are released.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[To serve, ladle the soup into bowls and drizzle with the mint butter. Serve warm.]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
